Detailed Description:
We are seeking a Tax Supervisor who will be involved in detailed review of tax provisions, distribution calculations, and tax returns prepared by staff. This individual will work closely with the head of the Tax Administration department and Staff Tax Accountant to drive the tax reporting and research functions.
In this role, the Tax Supervisor will perform the following responsibilities:
· Review monthly/quarterly distribution computations;
· Assist in review of annual capital gain estimates;
· Assist in review annual distribution computations;
· Review quarterly IRS compliance tests;
· Analyze securities transactions and calculate tax adjustments such as: wash sales, foreign currency gains/losses, etc. for tax footnotes for the Annual Reports;
· Analyze security book to tax differences due to real estate investment trusts, master limited partnerships, etc.
· Research tax characteristics of distributions from underlying investments and calculate tax adjustments or book reclassifications;
· Review dividend tax characteristic designations;
· Detail review federal and state tax returns for review (1120 RIC, Form 8613, etc.) prepared by staff;
· Work and communicate effectively with the Fund Administration and Fund Accounting departments to gather data and finalize tax provisions;
· Communicate effectively with external auditors to resolve tax reporting issues.
